      <Paragraph><Run Foreground="DarkGray">[The content included in this documentation is a sub-set of the Windows SDK, and may not be complete or current. Please see the online Windows SDK for current documentation.]</Run>

      </Paragraph>

      <Paragraph/>
      <Paragraph>This example shows how to manipulate the Title, Width, and Height of a window whose content tree a page resides in.    
      </Paragraph>

      <Paragraph FontSize="22">Example    
      </Paragraph>

      <Paragraph>If a page is intended to be loaded into more than one type of host container, it can't make assumptions about what members are implemented by its potential hosts because an implementation will typically differ from one host to the next. WindowTitle, WindowHeight, and WindowWidth are implemented to set the <Run FontWeight="Bold">Title</Run>
, <Run FontWeight="Bold">Width</Run>
, and <Run FontWeight="Bold">Height</Run>
 properties of the window whose content tree contains the page.    
      </Paragraph>

      <Table>
        <TableRowGroup>
          <TableRow>
            <TableCell>
              <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>C# </Run>

              </Paragraph>

            </TableCell>

          </TableRow>

          <TableRow>
            <TableCell>
              <Paragraph TextAlignment="Left" FontSize="8pt" FontFamily="Courier New" xml:space="preserve"><Run>// Set host window's Title, Width, and Height this.WindowTitle = "New Title Set by a Page!";this.WindowWidth = 500;this.WindowHeight = 500;</Run>
            
              </Paragraph>

            </TableCell>

          </TableRow>

        </TableRowGroup>

      </Table>

